in the new location and I assume paper.

819
00:35:10,440 --> 00:35:11,480
Yeah, paper counts.

820
00:35:12,440 --> 00:35:13,319
Amazing.

821
00:35:13,319 --> 00:35:15,239
Roll me two D6.

822
00:35:16,120 --> 00:35:17,240
Fire damage, please.

823
00:35:17,800 --> 00:35:19,400
That's gonna be five fire damage.

824
00:35:20,760 --> 00:35:24,360
Which is actually going to be 10 fire damage.

825
00:35:24,360 --> 00:35:28,920
And please tell me how this destroys this creature.

826
00:35:30,120 --> 00:35:30,760
Oh yeah.

827
00:35:31,800 --> 00:35:36,440
So as it assembles the flame core around the torch

828
00:35:36,440 --> 00:35:38,920
that is being held by Alydin's mage hand.

829
00:35:39,640 --> 00:35:42,520
I flick my hand out just ever so slightly

830
00:35:42,520 --> 00:35:44,520
just to like give it that little extra oomph

831
00:35:45,239 --> 00:35:47,880
splits the core open and just kind of like

832
00:35:47,880 --> 00:35:50,679
peels back in like layers of paper

833
00:35:50,679 --> 00:35:53,079
burning embers floating off

834
00:35:53,079 --> 00:35:57,079
and then that slowly engulfs the entire creature

835
00:35:57,079 --> 00:36:00,599
bringing it to just like a dusty ashy outline

836
00:36:00,599 --> 00:36:02,519
that's swirling around in circles

837
00:36:02,519 --> 00:36:05,639
and then ends into a spiraling pattern of ash on the floor.

838
00:36:07,559 --> 00:36:12,280
Oh, let's get some good audio of the clank of steel and stone

839
00:36:12,280 --> 00:36:13,640
that ended up hitting the ground

840
00:36:13,640 --> 00:36:15,240
after all the pages are burnt away.

841
00:36:15,240 --> 00:36:16,440
Yeah, love it.

842
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:18,920
Yeah, production.

843
00:36:20,200 --> 00:36:21,800
I'm the page master, bitch.

844
00:36:22,760 --> 00:36:23,960
Oh yeah.

845
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:30,519
The creature before you engulfs in flame

846
00:36:30,519 --> 00:36:33,080
and as described the room is now clear.

847
00:36:33,080 --> 00:36:34,840
All the pages have lit on fire

848
00:36:34,840 --> 00:36:36,840
and are burning up in the corners

849
00:36:36,840 --> 00:36:39,960
as everything is blowing around the space.

850
00:36:40,920 --> 00:36:44,840
You see some of the pages as they're burning

851
00:36:44,840 --> 00:36:48,199
the words crawling across its body slow

852
00:36:48,199 --> 00:36:50,119
and then freeze mid-letter

853
00:36:50,119 --> 00:36:52,280
and ink bleeds backwards

854
00:36:52,280 --> 00:36:54,920
into the seams of parchment and stone

855
00:36:54,920 --> 00:36:57,559
as if pulled by an unseen hand.

856
00:36:58,920 --> 00:37:01,159
The quill blade that fell to the ground

857
00:37:01,159 --> 00:37:03,720
softens and collapses into loose pages

858
00:37:03,720 --> 00:37:06,920
that scatter and also light on fire

859
00:37:06,920 --> 00:37:08,199
fade into dust

860
00:37:08,200 --> 00:37:10,600
and for a moment there's nothing.

861
00:37:12,600 --> 00:37:15,960
Then the room itself seemingly exhales.

862
00:37:17,320 --> 00:37:19,240
The shelves grind once more,

863
00:37:19,800 --> 00:37:21,880
not in threat this time,

864
00:37:21,880 --> 00:37:22,840
but in retreat.

865
00:37:23,560 --> 00:37:26,920
Stone books slide back into the walls

866
00:37:26,920 --> 00:37:29,720
and titles erasing themselves as they vanish

867
00:37:29,720 --> 00:37:32,040
until the chamber is bare

868
00:37:32,040 --> 00:37:34,280
save for that far wall.

869
00:37:34,920 --> 00:37:36,120
Where a door should be

870
00:37:37,079 --> 00:37:41,079
there is now only stone, unbroken, unmarked.

871
00:37:42,359 --> 00:37:45,639
A pause stretches almost too long

872
00:37:46,759 --> 00:37:48,119
and the floor shivers.

873
00:37:49,559 --> 00:37:51,880
Fine lines etch themselves outward

874
00:37:51,880 --> 00:37:54,359
from a single point at the chamber center

875
00:37:55,159 --> 00:37:58,119
not cracks but deliberate marks.

876
00:37:59,079 --> 00:38:00,440
A diagram emerges.

877
00:38:01,319 --> 00:38:04,359
Circles, angles, intersecting paths

878
00:38:04,360 --> 00:38:06,680
carved with impossible precision.

879
00:38:07,400 --> 00:38:08,039
It's a map.

880
00:38:09,559 --> 00:38:12,120
Vintersmouth sits at its heart

881
00:38:13,240 --> 00:38:16,120
not centered but pierced through

882
00:38:16,120 --> 00:38:19,640
as if something passes through the city

883
00:38:19,640 --> 00:38:21,160
rather than rests within it.

884
00:38:22,360 --> 00:38:25,079
Three lines extend outward.

885
00:38:25,960 --> 00:38:27,000
Two are still.

886
00:38:27,960 --> 00:38:29,320
The third flickers

887
00:38:29,320 --> 00:38:33,079
its edges blurring, shifting by the second

888
00:38:33,079 --> 00:38:34,679
sliding across the stone

889
00:38:34,679 --> 00:38:37,239
like a shadow that can't decide where to settle.

890
00:38:38,360 --> 00:38:41,719
As you watch, the line drifts slowly

891
00:38:42,840 --> 00:38:45,880
away from the city, away from here.

892
00:38:46,759 --> 00:38:47,960
The air grows heavy.

893
00:38:48,840 --> 00:38:50,759
Pressure builds behind your eyes

894
00:38:50,759 --> 00:38:53,000
like a thought trying to finish itself.

895
00:38:54,119 --> 00:38:55,079
You understand.

896
00:38:55,880 --> 00:38:58,199
This was never an entrance.

897
00:38:58,199 --> 00:38:59,159
It was a marker.

898
00:39:00,199 --> 00:39:01,559
A false index.

899
00:39:02,199 --> 00:39:02,840
A test.

900
00:39:03,480 --> 00:39:06,039
A way to see who would come looking

901
00:39:06,039 --> 00:39:07,880
and how they would read the record.

902
00:39:08,920 --> 00:39:11,559
Behind you, faint and distant,

903
00:39:11,559 --> 00:39:13,400
the sound of quills resume

904
00:39:13,960 --> 00:39:16,519
not here but elsewhere.

905
00:39:18,199 --> 00:39:21,079
The ink hesitates before writing

906
00:39:21,079 --> 00:39:22,279
as if considering you.

907
00:39:23,239 --> 00:39:25,400
The words appear uneven

908
00:39:25,400 --> 00:39:27,079
pressure changing mid-stroke.

909
00:39:28,599 --> 00:39:30,039
Seeker accepted.

910
00:39:30,119 --> 00:39:34,840
Then, after a pause, entry requires contribution.

911
00:39:36,360 --> 00:39:39,159
One final mark bleeds through the stone.

912
00:39:40,119 --> 00:39:43,880
Not words, but a name-shaped blur

913
00:39:44,440 --> 00:39:46,440
half-formed and familiar.

914
00:39:48,840 --> 00:39:51,639
The ground begins to shake and tremble

915
00:39:52,199 --> 00:39:53,719
and you look behind you

916
00:39:53,719 --> 00:39:57,480
at a path where again there wasn't one

917
00:39:57,480 --> 00:40:00,760
with light down at the end of the tunnel begins to form.

918
00:40:01,400 --> 00:40:03,800
Stone begins to fall from the walls

919
00:40:03,800 --> 00:40:07,320
as Alistair grabs you and says,

920
00:40:08,199 --> 00:40:10,760
he runs over to the wall

921
00:40:10,760 --> 00:40:14,760
and begins sketching the map that he sees

922
00:40:14,760 --> 00:40:18,519
and the room is collapsing down around you.

